<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Poker — Card Game Terms That Score"
  description="Poker and card game words valid in Scrabble with point values. BLUFF 13pts, FLUSH 11pts, WAGER 9pts, JOKER 16pts. Gambling vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble poker words, bluff scrabble points, flush scrabble word, wager scrabble, joker scrabble, card game words scrabble, gambling terms scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Poker — Card Game Terms That Score","description":"Poker and card game words valid in Scrabble with point values. BLUFF 13pts, FLUSH 11pts, WAGER 9pts, JOKER 16pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-poker"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BLUFF a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! BLUFF scores 13 points (B=3, L=1, U=1, F=4, F=4). It means to deceive opponents about your hand strength. The double-F contributes 8 of the 13 points, making it a strong consonant dump."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is FLUSH worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FLUSH scores 11 points (F=4, L=1, U=1, S=1, H=4). A poker hand where all five cards share the same suit. The F and H tiles together account for 8 of the 11 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is WAGER valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. WAGER scores 9 points (W=4, A=1, G=2, E=1, R=1) and means a bet placed on an uncertain outcome. The W tile provides nearly half the total score at 4 points."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Poker — Card Game Terms That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Poker terminology translates brilliantly to Scrabble. BLUFF uses the double-F for 13 points, FLUSH pairs F and H for 11, and WAGER puts the tricky W tile to productive use. Card game words are universally known, so they're easy to recall when you spot the right tiles on your rack.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JOKER (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BLUFF</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FLUSH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WAGER</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Poker Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JOKER — 16 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, O=1, K=5, E=1, R=1 · 5 letters · J+K power combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The wild card in a deck. JOKER combines J (8pts) and K (5pts) — two of the hardest consonants to use — into a single familiar word. At 3.2 points per tile, it's among the best ways to clear both premium tiles at once.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🃏 BLUFF</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · B=3, L=1, U=1, F=4, F=4 · Deceptive bet</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">♠️ FLUSH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · F=4, L=1, U=1, S=1, H=4 · Same-suit hand</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💰 WAGER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · W=4, A=1, G=2, E=1, R=1 · A bet</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎰 STAKE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · S=1, T=1, A=1, K=5, E=1 · Amount wagered</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Card Game Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RAISE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DEALT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TRUMP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FOLD</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHIPS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BLUFF dumps double-F:</span> Drawing two F tiles is painful. BLUFF uses both in one word for 13 points. If you have B, L, U and two F tiles, this is your go-to play every time.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FLUSH pairs F and H:</span> Both F (4pts) and H (4pts) are hard to place. FLUSH combines them for 11 points using common letters L, U, and S. The S at the end means it doesn't hook further (already ends in SH).</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WAGER clears W naturally:</span> W (4pts) is notoriously hard to use. WAGER puts it at the front with common tiles A, G, E, R. It also hooks to WAGERS or WAGERED for extensions.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Poker words specialise in <span class="text-white font-medium">F, H, W, and K tiles</span> — the mid-value consonants that plague many racks. BLUFF (FF), FLUSH (F+H), WAGER (W), JOKER (J+K), and STAKE (K) cover nearly every difficult 4-5 point tile in the game.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-games/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Games</span></a>
